Psalm 62-9 <pb/><t><f>ⓠ</f> Those of low estate are but a breath; </t><t>those of high estate <f>ⓡ</f>are a delusion; </t><t>in the balances they go up; </t><t><f>ⓢ</f>they are together lighter than a breath.</t>
Psalm 62-10 <t>Put no trust in extortion; </t><t><f>ⓣ</f>set no vain hopes on robbery; </t><t><f>ⓤ</f>if riches increase, set not your heart on them. </t>
